    <p class="page-body">I lived in Hershey, Pennsylvania for a short time and was deeply inspired by Milton Hershey's vision of making every visit "a moment of goodness." From the start, I knew two things: the app needed to honor his values, and it needed to solve a real problem for real visitors.</p>
    <div class="page-callout">"Make every visit a moment of goodness." — Milton Hershey</div>
  </div>

  <div class="page-section">
    <h2 class="page-section-title">The Problem</h2>
    <p class="page-body">Trip planning in the Hershey area is fragmented. Visitors currently rely on multiple apps to research attractions, check hours, navigate, and find deals — a stressful, time-consuming experience that contradicts Milton Hershey's vision.</p>
    <div class="page-two-col">
      <div class="page-card"><div class="page-card-label">The Pain</div><div class="page-card-body">Multiple apps, manual research, uncertain information → stressful, time-consuming, confusing.</div></div>
      <div class="page-card"><div class="page-card-label">Target Users</div><div class="page-card-body">Adults 20s–40s. Families, groups, and solo travelers for whom planning is overwhelming.</div></div>
