  <div class="page-section">
    <h2 class="page-section-title">MVP Scope & Key Decisions</h2>
    <p class="page-body">The first major decision: should the app be free or include paid features? To honor Milton Hershey's vision, I committed to a 100% free product — revenue through partnerships with local vendors and businesses, with a small percentage going back to Hershey.</p>
    <div class="page-feature-grid">
      <div class="page-feature"><div class="page-feature-title">AI Itinerary Builder</div><div class="page-feature-body">Generate a personalized day plan in seconds based on group size, time available, and interests.</div></div>
      <div class="page-feature"><div class="page-feature-title">Real-Time Park Data</div><div class="page-feature-body">Wait times, ride status, and crowd levels updated live to help users make decisions in the moment.</div></div>
      <div class="page-feature"><div class="page-feature-title">Contextual Discovery</div><div class="page-feature-body">Food, attractions, and deals surfaced based on location and itinerary context — not generic lists.</div></div>
      <div class="page-feature"><div class="page-feature-title">Local Partnerships</div><div class="page-feature-body">Featured local businesses and vendors within the app — the revenue model that keeps it free.</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="page-section">
    <h2 class="page-section-title">Research & Validation</h2>
    <p class="page-body">User testing revealed clear signals: people wanted one app over many, trusted AI-generated itineraries when they felt accurate and fast, and engaged with deals only when they felt relevant and timely.</p>
    <p class="page-body">But testing also exposed a critical problem — users were confused about whether the app was for Hersheypark specifically or the entire Hershey area. This was the turning point.</p>
    <div class="page-callout" style="border-left-color:rgba(180,60,60,0.4);background:rgba(180,60,60,0.04);color:rgba(120,30,30,0.8)">"My scope had drifted." — The biggest wound from testing was the park vs. area confusion.</div>
    <div class="page-two-col" style="margin-top:16px">
