      <div class="page-card"><div class="page-card-label">Users Struggled With</div><div class="page-card-body">Park vs. entire area confusion · Free vs. paid clarity · Backtracking in flows · AI not clearly responsive</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="page-section">
    <h2 class="page-section-title">The Pivot</h2>
    <p class="page-body">I made the call to broaden HersheyHome to the entire Hershey area — not just the park. This decision aligned with user expectations, supported more features like food and hotels, and better honored Milton Hershey's broader vision of the town itself.</p>
    <div class="page-steps">
      <div class="page-step"><span class="page-step-num">01</span><div>Realigned scope to the full Hershey area, not just Hersheypark</div></div>
      <div class="page-step"><span class="page-step-num">02</span><div>Redesigned "Build Your Day" flow with clearer group, duration, and interest inputs</div></div>
      <div class="page-step"><span class="page-step-num">03</span><div>Added color-coded time blocks (Morning / Afternoon / Evening) for the itinerary view</div></div>
      <div class="page-step"><span class="page-step-num">04</span><div>Made free vs. included vs. paid-ticket items visually distinct with badge labels</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="page-section">
